        "raw_content": "* **Definition:** The rate at which a biometric system **incorrectly grants access** to an unauthorized user — authenticating someone who should have been rejected. A high FAR means the system is too lenient. To reduce FAR, sensitivity is increased.\n  \n  > Como un guardia de seguridad tan confiado que deja entrar a cualquiera que tenga cara amable, sin verificar su identificación.\n\n---"
