        "raw_content": "* **Definition:** A modern malware delivery model that breaks the infection into two sequential phases to evade detection and establish persistent access:\n\n| Stage | Component | Function |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Stage 1** | **Dropper / Downloader / Shellcode** | Lightweight initial payload — executes when user clicks malicious link or opens infected file. Downloads and installs Stage 2. |\n| **Stage 2** | **RAT / Full Payload** | Full remote access Trojan or malware payload downloaded by Stage 1. Establishes C2 connection, spreads across network, escalates privileges. |\n\n* **Final phases after both stages:** → **Action on Objectives** (data exfiltration, encryption, sabotage) → **Concealment** (log deletion, evidence erasure)\n\n**Key terms within this model:**\n- **Dropper:** Malware designed to initiate or install other malware on the infected host\n- **Downloader:** Retrieves additional malicious tools after initial infection by a dropper\n- **Shellcode:** Lightweight code intended to execute an exploit on a target — often the initial payload\n\n> Como un equipo de asalto en dos oleadas: la primera entra sigilosamente y abre la puerta desde adentro, la segunda entra con toda la artillería y toma el control.\n\n---"
